column1: Who will win the 2019 Academy Award for Actor in a Leading Role?
column5: ['Christian Bale (Vice)', 'Bradley Cooper (A Star Is Born)', "Willem Dafoe (At Eternity's Gate)", 'Rami Malek (Bohemian Rhapsody)', 'Viggo Mortensen (Green Book)']

column6: Christian Bale is outstanding but Rami Malek (complete class act) MADE Bohemian Rhapsody (a good - not great - uplifting story).

Christian Bale has won the previous actor in a leading role award nominations at previous award shows. Including the Golden Globes and not only that but in the past winners of the actor in a leading role award have played real life people. This year Bale made a transformation to become Vice-President Dick Cheney which did very well in the box office making $55.7 million dollars. As for Rami Malek he won at the Golden Globes beating out Cooper and is played Queen frontman Freddie Mercury. However, A Star is Born and Coopers performance were very popular at the box office making $417 million dollars which is why I gave him at least 10%.
